Global War: Terminal Edition

A turn-based, terminal-based strategy game in Java where you control a country and compete against AI countries to dominate the world.

ğŸ“¦ Setup

Clone the repository (or download the .java file):

git clone <your-repo-url>
cd <repo-folder>


Make sure you have Java installed (Java 8+). Check with:

java -version
javac -version

ğŸ›  Compilation

Compile the game using javac:

javac GlobalWarGame.java


This will generate a GlobalWarGame.class file in the same folder.

â–¶ Running the Game

Run the game with:

java GlobalWarGame


You will see a welcome message and prompts to:

Enter your country name

Choose your starting region

The AI will automatically control other countries.

ğŸ® How to Play

The game is turn-based. On your turn, you can:

Build Military Units

Army: 10 resources

Navy: 15 resources

Air Force: 20 resources

Expand into New Regions

Capture unowned regions.

View Country Status

Check resources, military, and regions owned.

End Turn

Let AI take their turn.

ğŸ’£ AI Behavior

Builds units automatically.

Attempts to attack your or other AI regions.

AI attacks use a probabilistic system based on military power.

ğŸŒ World Events

Events happen randomly after each turn (30% chance).

Examples:

Economic Boom (+resources)

Economic Crisis (-resources)

Natural Disaster (-resources)

Technological Breakthrough (+resources)

ğŸ† Victory Condition

You win if you control more than half of all regions.

Game over occurs if your country loses all regions.

âš™ï¸ Game Mechanics

Military Power = Army*5 + Navy*8 + AirForce*12

Each region is represented by a Region object with ownership.

AI uses simple strategy to expand and attack.

Resources are required to build units.

